From The Daily
In Age of Miracles, Packy and Julia outline the several blockers to major a=
doption of nuclear in the U.S.:
Regulatory Hurdles: Stringent regulation makes building nuclear slow and ex=
pensive to build more nuclear capacity.=20
Public Perception and Opposition: The public fears nuclear due to historica=
l accidents and misconceptions on safety.=20
Economic Challenges: High upfront costs and and execution risk make nuclear=
 less attractive then alternatives.=20
Technical and Manufacturing Bottlenecks: Current buildout are slow, expensi=
ve, and impede rapid scaling.
In a recent episode of The New York Time=E2=80=99s podcast =E2=80=9CThe Dai=
ly,=E2=80=9D they discuss how and to what extent each of these blockers are=
 starting to erode and why that=E2=80=99s important in the U.S. today. =E2=
=80=9CThe Daily=E2=80=9D dedicating an episode to nuclear momentum is impor=
tant in and of itself, in that it can further help swing blocker #2 above: =
public perception of nuclear. The podcast gets nearly ~1M downloads per epi=
sode and consistently ranks as one of the top 5 podcasts in the world. Age =
of Miracles definitely nuked pilled some folks, but =E2=80=94 and I mean no=
 offense to big bro here =E2=80=94 it wasn=E2=80=99t getting 1M downloads p=
er episode. There=E2=80=99s now ~1M more folks that are probably having som=
e version of the =E2=80=9Cwait, so nuclear isn=E2=80=99t this dangerous acc=
ident waiting to happen, but is actually this safe, clean source of energy =
that we need to hit our climate goals?=E2=80=9D phenomena. That=E2=80=99s a=
 good thing.
The pod itself describes the already ongoing shift in public perception, ch=
anges in regulatory posture, how startups like Bill Gate=E2=80=99s TerraPow=
er are making big advances, and how new approaches to building nuclear are =
overcoming its economic challenges. This was a largely pro-nuclear pod=E2=
=80=A6and a nuke-pilled New York Times is a good thing for the future of nu=
clear in this country.=20
P.S. In its Three Morning Takes (which you should subscribe to [ https://su=
bstack.com/redirect/df85c818-1492-4f8d-846d-8a36d5e34c74?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3=
QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU ]), Pirate Wires [ https:/=
