n significantly extend the healthy lifespan of mice, by as much as 20%. The=
 treatment reduced cancer deaths and other diseases related to inflammation=
 and poor metabolism, which are common in ageging. When older mice (equival=
ent to the 55+ in human years) were treated with the IL-11 treatment, their=
 median lifespan increased up to 25%.</p><p style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55)=
; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">IL-11 (interleuk=
in-11) is a protein that has been traditionally misunderstood. Initially th=
ought to be anti-inflammatory, recent research has shown that IL-11 actuall=
y promotes fibrosis (scarring of tissues) and inflammation. Oopsie daisy&#8=
230;little mixup! Fibrosis and chronic inflammation are key contributors to=
 many age-related diseases and conditions. Inhbiting IL-11, thus, can slow =
down or prevent some of these diseases and conditions, or at least that&#82=
17;s what the early mice trials show.</p><p style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55)=
; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">Adding IL-11 tre=
